[X] tar Command List

[\] sudo apt install tar
[/] Install tar on Debian/Ubuntu

[\] sudo dnf install tar
[/] Install tar on Fedora

[\] sudo pacman -S tar
[/] Install tar on Arch Linux

[\] brew install gnu-tar
[/] Install GNU tar on macOS using Homebrew

[\] tar -cvf archive.tar file.txt
[/] Create tar archive from file

[\] tar -cvf archive.tar folder/
[/] Create tar archive from folder

[\] tar -xvf archive.tar
[/] Extract tar archive

[\] tar -xvf archive.tar -C /path/to/folder
[/] Extract archive to specific directory

[\] tar -tvf archive.tar
[/] List contents of archive

[\] tar -rvf archive.tar newfile.txt
[/] Append file to existing archive

[\] tar -uvf archive.tar file.txt
[/] Update changed file in archive

[\] tar -cvzf archive.tar.gz folder/
[/] Create gzip compressed archive

[\] tar -xvzf archive.tar.gz
[/] Extract gzip archive

[\] tar -cvjf archive.tar.bz2 folder/
[/] Create bzip2 compressed archive

[\] tar -xvjf archive.tar.bz2
[/] Extract bzip2 archive

[\] tar -cvJf archive.tar.xz folder/
[/] Create xz compressed archive

[\] tar -xvJf archive.tar.xz
[/] Extract xz archive

[\] tar --exclude="*.log" -cvf archive.tar folder/
[/] Exclude files by pattern

[\] tar -cvf backup.tar /home/user --absolute-names
[/] Archive with absolute paths

[\] tar -xvf archive.tar file.txt
[/] Extract specific file from archive

[\] tar -cvf - folder/ | ssh host "cat > backup.tar"
[/] Stream archive over SSH

[\] tar -xvf - < archive.tar
[/] Extract from stdin

[\] tar --delete -f archive.tar file.txt
[/] Remove file from archive

[\] tar --help
[/] Show help menu

[\] tar --version
[/] Show tar version
